Let $ ABC$ be an equilateral triangle inscribed in circle $ O$. $ M$ is a point on arc $ BC$. Lines $ \overline{AM}$, $ \overline{BM}$, and $ \overline{CM}$ are drawn. Then $ AM$ is:\\

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
defaultpen(linewidth(.8pt));
unitsize(2cm);

pair O = origin;
pair B = (1,0);
pair C = dir(120);
pair A = dir(240);
pair M = dir(90 - 18);

draw(Circle(O,1));
draw(A--C--M--B--cycle);
draw(B--C);
draw(A--M);
dot(O);

label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,E);
label("$M$",M,NE);
label("$C$",C,NW);
label("$O$",O,SE);
\end{asy}
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ \text{equal to }{BM + CM}\qquad \textbf{(B)}\ \text{less than }{BM + CM}\qquad \textbf{(C)}\ \text{greater than }{BM + CM}\qquad$\\
$ \textbf{(D)}\ \text{equal, less than, or greater than }{BM + CM}\text{, depending upon the position of }{ {M}\qquad}$\\
$ \textbf{(E)}\ \text{none of these}$
